        <content><![CDATA[ <h1 class="title topictitle1">Incident form</h1>  <div class="body conbody">  <p class="p">The Incident form captures information about an incident. This information is used to quickly   restore normal service operations. The information is also helpful for a post-resolution analysis   to reduce the impact of similar future incidents. </p>  <p class="p">Review the Incident form to determine whether it aligns with your business needs. </p>  <p class="p">To modify the form layout, click the context menu and select <span class="ph menucascade"><span class="ph uicontrol">Configure</span> &gt; <span class="ph uicontrol">Form Layout</span></span>.</p> </div> <div class="related-links"><div class="relinfo"><div class="reltitle">Related information<br /><div><a class="link" href="https://docs.servicenow.com/?context&#61;CSHelp:Form-Design&amp;version&#61;kingston" target="_blank">Form design</a></div><div><a class="link" href="https://docs.servicenow.com/?context&#61;CSHelp:Form-Layout&amp;version&#61;kingston" target="_blank">Form layout</a></div><div><a class="link" href="https://docs.servicenow.com/?context&#61;CSHelp:Incident-Management&amp;version&#61;kingston" target="_blank">Incident Management</a></div></div></div></div>]]></content>
